HEADWORD: Gallnut
<hw>Gall"nut`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A
round gall produced on the leaves and shoots of various species of the
oak tree. See <er>Gall</er>, and <er>Nutgall</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

